{"lemma":"إِطارٌ","slug":"إِطارٌ","root":"#.ط.ر","root_slug":"_-ط-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ط-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n905"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"frame, framework (also from doors and eyewear, and about things that are called hoop or tire in English, and likewise figuratively)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cadre"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a window","tags":["dated","neologism"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔi.tˤaːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n905","headword_ar":"اـِطَارٌ","root":"ATr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that surrounds another thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K:) as the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoop"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tambourine, (A, Mgh, TA,) and of a sieve. (S, A, Mgh, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ring of hair surrounding the head, the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":67},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle of it being bald."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branches of a vine, bent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wreathed, so as to form a covering over-head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uTorapN","text_ar":"اُطْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iTaAru AlHaAfiri","text_ar":"اـِطَارُ الحَافِرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The part of the hoof of a horse or the like which surrounds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extends around, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oEar","text_ar":"اَشْعَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q.v.]. (S.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iTaAru Al$~afapi","text_ar":"اـِطَارُ الشَّفَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, &c.) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounding the lip:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the part that separates between the lip and the hairs of the mustache:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the edge of the upper lip, between the lip itself and the parts where the hair grows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rising edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ridge, between the part where the mustache is clipped and the lip, intermixing with the mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd.) The Muslim should clip his mustache so that this part shall appear. (Msb, TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iTaAru bayotK","text_ar":"اـِطَارُ بَيْتٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing resembling a zone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belt, of a tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iTaAri mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"اـِطَارِ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circle, of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A_iTaArN libaniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"هُمْ اـِطَارٌ لِبَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They have alighted and taken up their abode"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that they form a ring"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around the sons of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","Mgh","TA","IAth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}